Cookies are small pieces of text saved by websites to your computer. Cookies are how your computer remembers things you’ve already done on the internet and are an important part of making modern websites work properly. Because cookies may contain information about your browsing habits, some people prefer to turn them off entirely. However, turning off cookies can prevent websites from working the way you expect. Essential cookies These cookies are critical to the functioning of this website and cannot be disabled through this control panel. They don’t contain any information about your identity. They can be disabled through your browser, but doing so could cause some parts of this website to stop working. I worked at Mole Hall Wildlife Park throughout my teens and gained a vast knowledge of the natural world and its inhabitants. Michaela and I first set eyes on Pannington Hall farm in 2002. At just 24 years of age we dreamt of a full restoration, returning the totally derelict farm back to a fully working, thriving livestock farm. Our vision was to only use traditional, free-range farming methods with 100% traceability, rearing rare and domestic breeds from the UK. We focused initially on the Essex pig with a bloodline so rare it was classed as extinct! In 2003, The Essex Pig Company was born. Creating a small onsite butchery and farm shop, Michaela and I began turning our forest-fledged, free-range pork into premium, rare-breed sausages and bacon. At that time I was also invited to take part in a BBC documentary that followed our escapades and endeavours (‘Jimmy’s Farm’) and soon the farm became a destination for tourists and locals alike. Since then, it’s developed beyond our wildest dreams! Jimmy’s Farm is now home to a wildlife park, restaurant, wedding venue, vegetable and flower gardens, farm shop and wonderful retail concessions. ‘Sharing the Good Life’ encapsulates our belief that the natural world should be accessible and available to all and we hope that you will join us in creating your own wild, imaginative and incredible adventure. From humble beginnings… Jimmy x Tickets Events Membership Reservations Meet the Team Jimmy Doherty, CEO Michaela Doherty, Managing Director Stevie Sheppard , Park Director The Executive Team Sophie Ryder , Head of Animal Operations Gemma Marriage , Head of Land and Native Conservation Kirsty Dupée , Head of Commercial Operations Sharon Scott, Head of Finance Lauren Dodman , Head of Visitor Experience Gary Hamblion, Head of Maintenance Behind everything we do is an exceptional team. None of our success would be possible without the passion, dedication and expertise of the incredible staff who bring our mission to life every single day. Whether caring for animals, welcoming guests, growing produce, or supporting operations behind the scenes, Team Jimmys is the heart and soul of everything we do.
